The 7on7 camp is a great opportunity for young athletes to showcase their skills and compete with other talented players in a safe and structured environment. With the support of Councilwoman Johnson and Mr. Walker, this tournament has become even more exciting for the players, coaches, and fans alike. The generous donation of $5000 to the winning team will not only provide a much-needed boost to their morale but also help them invest in their future training and development. Furthermore, Councilwoman Johnson's continued efforts to pour into the community and support initiatives like this camp are truly commendable and inspiring. It is through such acts of kindness and generosity that we can build a stronger and more united community for all.
